{#
    Item Taxonomy Badges -- the assigned category as a badge and tags as chips for one item.

    Renders the item's category label (if any) as a coloured Bulma tag and each assigned tag as a
    light chip, labelled in the guest's locale with source-locale fallback. Renders nothing when the
    item has neither a category nor tags, so callers can include it unconditionally. Reads the
    assignments through item_category_label() / item_tag_labels() (ItemTaxonomyExtension).

    Used in:    dishes / books / films list layouts and detail pages
    Parameters:
        - itemType (string, required) -- registry key of the item type (e.g. 'dish')
        - itemId   (int, required)    -- id of the item whose assignments to render
    Depends on: item_category_label(), item_tag_labels() (ItemTaxonomyExtension)
#}
{% set category = item_category_label(itemType, itemId) %}
{% set tags = item_tag_labels(itemType, itemId) %}
{% if category is not empty or tags is not empty %}
    <div class="tags taxonomy-badges">
        {% if category is not empty %}
            <span class="tag is-info is-light">{{ category }}</span>
        {% endif %}
        {% for tag in tags %}
            <span class="tag is-light">{{ tag }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
{% endif %}
